==English==

===Etymology===
From Hawaiian, meaning ''love''<!--, when using it as a greeting it can mean "hello" or "good-bye", also "I love you". The reply is ''"Aloha (iä) 'oe"''.-->

===Pronuncation===
Ălōhă

===Interjection===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Aloha'''

# [[hello]] 
# [[goodbye]] 
# [[I love you]] 

